@peterweb2005 Thanks for reporting this issue.
@huycozy Thank for the repro and the links you found.

This is related to the change in https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/150278.
Previously the M3 defaults were ignored (`ThemeData.hintColor` was meant for M2 and its default are compliant with M3 specification).

I will try to figure out a way to use `ThemeData.hintColor` only if it is provided. But this is not straightforward because, if it is not provided, the value is initialized directly in the `ThemeData` factory (see https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/9b8470197f4205d05d8507850b65e6d9f2fda105/packages/flutter/lib/src/material/theme_data.dart#L448).
For the moment, the solution is to is to replace `ThemeData.hintColor` usage with `ThemeData.InputDecortationTheme.hintStyle`

<details><summary>Updated code sample</summary>

```dart

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(
    MaterialApp(
      home: const MyApp(),
      theme: ThemeData(
        // hintColor: Colors.red,
        inputDecorationTheme: const InputDecorationTheme(hintStyle: TextStyle(color: Colors.red)),
      ),
    ),
  );
}

class MyApp extends StatefulWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  State<MyApp> createState() => _MyAppState();
}

class _MyAppState extends State<MyApp> {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return const Scaffold(
      body: Center(
        child: TextField(
          decoration: InputDecoration(
            hintText: 'Enter your name',
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

``` 
</details> 

@justinmc @guidezpl 
Do you think we should revert https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/150278 while figuring out if we can provide a way to use `ThemeData.hintColor` only if provided or, maybe, decide if we want to proceed with the deprecation initiated in https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/116346.

