comments:
This is happening because right clicks are handled by the browser (not framework) on web in order to support native context menus.  When the user right clicks, the underlying input receives it, and that state is synced with the framework.

The problem here is that the scroll state between the underlying input and the framework is not synced, so we'll get into a weird state when you scroll down to the further lines.  You end up right clicking "Line 3" on the underlying input even though the framework has appeared to scroll that out of view.  The solution is to sync the scroll states between the browser and framework. 

@mdebbar and I had a discussion about this as something that would need to be fixed for https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/120613 - so I'll mark this as a P1.

issues.body:
### Steps to reproduce

If a `DropdownMenu` widget by coincidence is aligned with the top of the virtual keyboard, it does not expand as expected.

In our app this happens on some devices in the registration screen, there is a dropdown to select countries and on for instance iPhone 12 this widget is perfectly aligned with the top of the keyboard and the users do not get the list when the input field gets the focus.

The attached sample code is a minimal working example for an iPhone 15 screen as in the video. It is based on the official sample code for the DropdownMenu widget.

### Expected results

DropdownMenu entries should expand.

### Actual results

DropdownMenu entries do not expand/not visible.

### Code sample

<details open><summary>Code sample</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
void main() {
  runApp(const DropdownMenuExample());
}
enum ColorLabel {
  blue('Blue', Colors.blue),
  pink('Pink', Colors.pink),
  green('Green', Colors.green),
  yellow('Orange', Colors.orange),
  grey('Grey', Colors.grey);
  const ColorLabel(this.label, this.color);
  final String label;
  final Color color;
}
class DropdownMenuExample extends StatefulWidget {
  const DropdownMenuExample({super.key});
  @override
  State<DropdownMenuExample> createState() => _DropdownMenuExampleState();
}
class _DropdownMenuExampleState extends State<DropdownMenuExample> {
  final TextEditingController colorController = TextEditingController();
  ColorLabel? selectedColor;
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      theme: ThemeData(
        useMaterial3: true,
        colorSchemeSeed: Colors.green,
      ),
      home: Scaffold(
        body: SafeArea(
          child: ListView(
            children: <Widget>[
              TextField(),
              Padding(
                padding: const EdgeInsets.symmetric(vertical: 20),
                child: Row(
                  mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.center,
                  children: <Widget>[
                    DropdownMenu<ColorLabel>(
                      initialSelection: ColorLabel.green,
                      controller: colorController,
                      requestFocusOnTap: true,
                      label: const Text('Color'),
                      onSelected: (ColorLabel? color) {
                        setState(() {
                          selectedColor = color;
                        });
                      },
                      dropdownMenuEntries: ColorLabel.values
                          .map<DropdownMenuEntry<ColorLabel>>(
                              (ColorLabel color) {
                        return DropdownMenuEntry<ColorLabel>(
                          value: color,
                          label: color.label,
                          enabled: color.label != 'Grey',
                          style: MenuItemButton.styleFrom(
                            foregroundColor: color.color,
                          ),
                        );
                      }).toList(),
                    ),
                    const SizedBox(height: 710),
                  ],
                ),
              ),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
